Installing LN node in Amazon linux

# Source:
https://dev.lightning.community/guides/installation/#installation

# More info:
https://github.com/bcongdon/awesome-lightning-network

## Provisioning

- Launch one T2 micro instance, using Ubuntu 14.04 LTS AMI.
- Open SSH and Bitcoin Protocol TCP ports: 22, 8333.
- Attach 40GB EBS (General-Purpose SSD) volume for blockchain storage to /dev/sdf.

1. Create basic instance with 64gb of disk
2. sudo yum update && sudo yum upgrade
3. sudo amazon-linux-extras install golang1.11
4. append to .bash_profile
  # Golang
  export GOPATH=~/go
  export PATH=$PATH:$GOPATH/bin
5. reload profile `source .bash_profile`
6. install lnd
  go get -d github.com/lightningnetwork/lnd
  cd $GOPATH/src/github.com/lightningnetwork/lnd
  make && make install
7. updating lnd
  cd $GOPATH/src/github.com/lightningnetwork/lnd
  git pull
  make clean && make && make install
8. check the installation
  make test

9. Install bitcoin core full node, with a pruned chain
https://medium.com/coinmonks/bitcoin-lightning-network-run-your-node-at-home-for-fun-and-no-profit-da5b61be2ba9

9a. Add 2Gb of swap
  sudo dd if=/dev/zero of=/opt/swap bs=1M count=2048
  sudo mkswap /opt/swap
  sudo swapon /opt/swap

9b. Add swap to /etc/fstab
  /opt/swap swap swap defaults 0 0

9c. Download Bitcoin Core
  # Variables setup
  BITCOIND_VERSION=0.17.1
  ARCH=x86_64-linux-gnu
  BITCOIND_ARCHIVE=bitcoin-${BITCOIND_VERSION}-${ARCH}.tar.gz

  # Download bitcoin core
  cd /tmp
  wget https://bitcoincore.org/bin/bitcoin-core-${BITCOIND_VERSION}/${BITCOIND_ARCHIVE}
  wget https://bitcoincore.org/bin/bitcoin-core-${BITCOIND_VERSION}/SHA256SUMS.asc
  wget https://bitcoin.org/laanwj-releases.asc

  # Validate download
  SHA256=`grep "${BITCOIND_ARCHIVE}" SHA256SUMS.asc | awk '{print $1}'`
  echo $SHA256
  echo "$SHA256 ${BITCOIND_ARCHIVE}" | sha256sum -c -
  gpg --import ./laanwj-releases.asc
  gpg --verify SHA256SUMS.asc

  tar -xzf ${BITCOIND_ARCHIVE}
  sudo install -m 0755 -o root -g root -t /usr/local/bin bitcoin-${BITCOIND_VERSION}/bin/*
  rm -rf /tmp/*
  bitcoind --version
